<span id="freeTextContainer38400583343317445">Nocturnes: Five Stories of Music and Nightfall, Kazuo Ishiguro <br/>Nocturnes: Five Stories of Music and Nightfall is a 2009 collection of short fiction by Kazuo Ishiguro. After six novels, it is Ishiguro first collection of short stories, though described by the publisher as a &quot;story cycle&quot;. As the subtitle suggests, each of the five stories focuses on music and musicians, and the close of day. The hardback was published by Faber and Faber in the United Kingdom on 7 May 2009 and in the United States</span>
  <span id="freeText38400583343317445" style="display:none">Nocturnes: Five Stories of Music and Nightfall, Kazuo Ishiguro <br />Nocturnes: Five Stories of Music and Nightfall is a 2009 collection of short fiction by Kazuo Ishiguro. After six novels, it is Ishiguro first collection of short stories, though described by the publisher as a "story cycle". As the subtitle suggests, each of the five stories focuses on music and musicians, and the close of day. The hardback was published by Faber and Faber in the United Kingdom on 7 May 2009 and in the United States by Knopf in September 2009.<br />Five stories: "Crooner"; "Come Rain or Come Shine"; "Malvern Hills"; "Nocturne"; and "Cellists".<br />تاریخ نخستین خوانش: بیست و نهم ماه نوامبر سال 2011 میلادی<br />عنوان: شبانه ها: پنج داستان درباره موسیقی و شعر؛ کازوئو ایشی گورو؛ مترجم: خجسته کیهان؛ تهران، کتاب پارسه، 1389؛ در 198 ص؛ شابک: 9786005733068؛ <br />مترجم: علیرضا کیوانی نژاد؛ تهران، چشمه، 1389؛ در 223 ص؛ شابک: 9789643627331؛<br />داستانهای: آوازخوان؛ چه بارانی باشد چه آفتابی؛ شبانه؛ نوازندگان ویلون سل؛ تپه های مالورن؛ ا. شربیانی</span>
