    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2719512601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11188993976010865218">A short time ago, I made a decision to read several books with music as part of their themes. I decided to start by reading <i>Nocturnes</i>, and have since regretted that choice. I found nothing in the music recounted in any of the stories that I could relate to in the least, I found the characters uninteresting, and the writing seemed simplistic (and not in any positive sense of that word). Two of the stories, &quot;Come Rain or Come Shine&quot; and &quot;Nocturne&quot; could easily have served as the plotlines for chee</span>
  <span id="freeText11188993976010865218" style="display:none">A short time ago, I made a decision to read several books with music as part of their themes. I decided to start by reading <i>Nocturnes</i>, and have since regretted that choice. I found nothing in the music recounted in any of the stories that I could relate to in the least, I found the characters uninteresting, and the writing seemed simplistic (and not in any positive sense of that word). Two of the stories, "Come Rain or Come Shine" and "Nocturne" could easily have served as the plotlines for cheesy TV movies.<br />Several of my GR friends think much more highly of this book than I do, while others seem to have had much the same experience I did. That's part of why we're here - to agree, to disagree, and to learn from both of those experiences.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11188993976010865218" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


